Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) could be alternative energy conversion devices due to their simple fabrication process and low cost.
Titulo: Cerium and ruthenium co-doped La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ as a high-efficiency electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Herein, perovskite La0.6Ce0.1Sr0.3Fe0.95Ru0.05O3-d (LCSFR) was synthesized and evaluated as a high-performance electrode for SSOFCs based on the electrolyte of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-d (LSGM).
Titulo: Cerium and ruthenium co-doped La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ as a high-efficiency electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: LCSFR retains their stable perovskite crystal structure in both reducing and oxidizing atmospheres, though a minor amount of LaSrFeO4 phase is present under reducing conditions.
Titulo: Cerium and ruthenium co-doped La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ as a high-efficiency electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Morphology investigation shows that homogeneously dispersed Ru metallic nanoparticles are exsolved on the surface of LCSFR after being reduced.
Titulo: Cerium and ruthenium co-doped La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ as a high-efficiency electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The polarization resistance (Rp) of LCSFR-CGO (Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-d) is about 0.11 U,cm2 at 800 degrees C in air, while the value of Rp for LCSFR-CGO in wet H2 (3% H2O) increases up to 0.32 U,cm2.
Titulo: Cerium and ruthenium co-doped La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ as a high-efficiency electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The symmetrical LCSFR-CGO|LSGM|LCSFR-CGO cell demonstrates a performance with an open circuit potential (OCV) of 1.07 V and a maximum peak power density of 904 mW/cm2 at 800 degrees C using wet H2 as the fuel.
Titulo: Cerium and ruthenium co-doped La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ as a high-efficiency electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This high performance indicates that LCSFR is a candidate electrode for SSOFCs.
Titulo: Cerium and ruthenium co-doped La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-δ as a high-efficiency electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell
